(由 Google 提供翻譯) DIY旅遊是兒童的好經歷（最好是4歲以上）。我們親自製作了自己的豆腐（豆花和豆腐），並且幾乎立即嚐到了最終產品。與在該區域的所有工廠參觀一樣，每個門票都會有一張折扣券，用於在他們的商店購買，但他們並不特別咄咄逼人（我強烈推薦皮蛋皮蛋 - 我最好的之一）嚐到了，我並不是它的粉絲。）此外，每張門票都有權在下一棟樓的零售角落買一瓶豆漿。請提前打電話預約，因為它似乎是一個非常受歡迎的學校遊覽場所，即使是當地的孩子。門票費用為每人150迪拉姆（3歲及以上）。(原始評論)The DIY tours were good experiences for children (preferably above age of 4). We had our hands on at making our own soy beancurds (豆花 and 豆腐), and got to taste the end products almost immediately. As with all factory tours in the precinct, there will be a discount voucher for each ticket for purchases made in their store but they're not particularly pushy about it (I do highly recommend the preserved eggs 皮蛋 - one of the best I've tasted and I'm not exactly a fan of it to begin with). Also each ticket is entitled to a bottle of soy milk at the retail corner in the next building. Do call ahead to book an appointment as it seems like a very popular venue for school excursion even for local kids.Ticket costs TWD150 per head (for age 3 and above).

(由 Google 提供翻譯) 這絕對不是那些困擾你並向你推銷你不需要的東西的遊客工廠。這是一個合作社，提供有關食物的互動教育計劃。我們家人學會瞭如何在2小時內製作豆腐，軟豆腐和鹹蛋。林老師是食品行業友好，幽默，知識淵博的人才。我們非常感謝他從他那裡學到了很多東西。(原始評論)This is absolutely NOT those tourists factories that trap you and sell you things that you don't need. This is a cooperative that offers interactive educational programs about food. Our family learned how to make bean curd, soft soya bean curd and salted eggs within 2 hours.
